// Changing foreground / background color. <small>(Hex works too)</small>
```SetForegroundColour ("Black") ``` <small>// (if you want to change your font color in general, use this.)</small>
```SetBackgroundColour ("Red") ```

// Changing FONT (and size) in game.
```SetFontName ("'Courier New', Courier, monospace")```
```SetWebFontName ("Special Elite")```
```SetFontSize (12)```


<br><br>
// Background image
There's more ways than one but the one I have found most reliable is using CSS.

<br>
<font color=red>Edit:</font> Using CSS I've remodelled the entire interface (the location of panes and the graphical structure of the 'page' etc) so I'm not 100% the below code works in a 'template game'. Do try. =)

<br>


```
div#gameBorder {
    background-attachment: fixed !important;
    background-image: url("http://url/pic.png") !important;
    width: auto !important;
} 
```
<small>(I have <b>lots</b> of stuff in the #gameBorder div but I removed the stuff that doesn't have anything to do with the background image for easier reading.)</small>

Hope this helps.

